criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Office blood pressure between 130-179 and 80-110 mmHg;

          -  Non-engaged in structured programs of exercise for the last 3 months since the
             begining of this study;

          -  Verified ability to exercise.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Underlying cardiovascular disease previously diagnosticated by a doctor, occurred in
             the last 24 months, such as: acute myocardial infarction, angina, stroke or heart
             failure;

          -  Diseases that reduce life expectancy;

          -  Smokers and ex-smokers for less than six months;

          -  BMI > 39.9 kg/mÂ²

          -  diabetic proliferative retinopathy.
